parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Defects (Recall Delays and Unavailability of Parts)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays in recall repairs can lead to potential safety risks, as the defects may cause electrical system failures, airbag malfunctions, or other issues that can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Notification of recalls
but parts are not available
or dealers are not scheduling appointments for repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Advanced Safety Features Malfunction (Cruise Control and Forward Collision Avoidance)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning advanced safety features can increase the risk of accidents, as the vehicle may not respond as intended in emergency situations.
symptoms: Cruise control and Forward Collision Avoidance systems do not activate as needed
even when driving at moderate speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Backup Camera and Lane Watch Defects
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Defective backup cameras and lane watch systems can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries, especially when reversing or changing lanes.
symptoms: Backup camera and lane watch systems are unable to be seen in daylight
or the display is unclear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Miscellaneous RV Defects (Upper Door Lock, Kitchen Faucet, TV, and Mirrors)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: These defects can cause inconvenience, discomfort, and potentially lead to safety issues if left unaddressed.
symptoms: Upper door lock is inoperative
kitchen faucet leaks
TV needs to be replaced
and mirrors are insufficient for viewing what is being towed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Cruise Control and Adaptive Cruise Control System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning Cruise Control and Adaptive Cruise Control system can cause inconvenience, distraction, and potentially lead to accidents, as the driver may need to constantly adjust speed and distance from other vehicles.
symptoms: The Cruise Control system does not engage or disengage properly
the system displays blank or blinking cursors on the dashboard monitor
the system fails to maintain a set speed
the system does not adapt to changing traffic conditions
the system is inconsistent or unreliable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty brake assist sensor can cause the brake assist system to malfunction, leading to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially, accidents.
symptoms: The "Brake Assist Inoperable - See Owner's Manual" message is displayed on the dashboard
the warning light remains illuminated
the brake assist system does not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Recall Repair Parts for Trailer Hitches
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed or unavailability of recall repair parts for trailer hitches can lead to a prolonged period of driving with a potentially unsafe vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Notification of recall
inability to obtain repair parts
delayed or unavailable repair
lack of assistance from manufacturer.
